    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 2004 Porsche 911 GT3, featuring the legendary 3.6L Mezger-designed flat-six. This high-revving power unit utilizes a dry-sump lubrication system and titanium connecting rods to achieve its 8,200 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a G96/96 six-speed manual transaxle with a factory-equipped limited-slip differential. The chassis remains impeccably rigid, retaining all original factory welds and a flawless underside. Suspension geometry is dialed to factory specifications, utilizing adjustable coilover dampers for surgical turn-in. Braking is handled by six-piston monoblock calipers clamping cross-drilled rotors, showing zero thermal cycling fatigue. This specimen represents a rare opportunity to acquire a pure, analog driving machine in preserved, showroom state.",
